Čiovo.label: Čiovo
Čiovo.description: Čiovo is a small island located off the Adriatic coast in Croatia with an area of 28.8 square kilometres, population of 6,071 inhabitants and its highest peak is 218 m. Wikipedia

Šolta.label: Šolta
Šolta.description: Šolta is an island in Croatia. It is situated in the Adriatic Sea in the central Dalmatian archipelago, west of the island of Brač, south of Split and east of the Drvenik islands. Its area is 58.98 km² and it has a population of 1,700. Wikipedia

Admiralty Island.label: Admiralty Island
Admiralty Island.description: Admiralty Island is an island in the Alexander Archipelago in Southeast Alaska, at 57°44′N 134°20′W﻿ / ﻿57.733°N 134.333°W. It is 145 km long and 56 km wide with an area of 4,264.1 km², making it the seventh largest island in the United States and ... Wikipedia

Akimiski Island.label: Akimiski Island
Akimiski Island.description: Akimiski Island is the largest island in James Bay, Canada, which is part of the Qikiqtaaluk Region of the territory of Nunavut. It has an area of 3,001 km², making it the 163rd largest island in the world, and Canada's 29th largest island. Wikipedia

Alnön.label: Alnön
Alnön.description: Alnön is an island in the Gulf of Bothnia just outside Sundsvall in Medelpad, Sweden. It has an area of 65 km² and a permanent population of 8,298, although its summertime inhabitants are about twice that number. Wikipedia

Anholt (Denmark).label: Anholt
Anholt (Denmark).description: Anholt is a Danish island in the Kattegat, midway between Jutland and Sweden, with 171 permanent residents as of 1 January 2010. It is seven miles long and about four miles wide at its widest and covers an area of 21,75 km². Wikipedia

Anticosti Island.label: Anticosti
Anticosti Island.description: Anticosti Island is an island in Quebec, Canada, at the outlet of the Saint Lawrence River into the Gulf of Saint Lawrence, between 49° and 50° N., and between 61° 40' and 64° 30' W. At 7,892.52 km² in ... Wikipedia

Aquidneck Island.label: Aquidneck Island
Aquidneck Island.description: Aquidneck Island, located in the U.S. state of Rhode Island, is the largest island in Narragansett Bay. The island's official name is Rhode Island, and the common use of the name "Aquidneck Island" helps distinguish the island from the state. Wikipedia

Arapawa Island.label: Arapawa Island
Arapawa Island.description: Arapawa Island is a small island located in the Marlborough Sounds, at the north east tip of the South Island of New Zealand. The island has a land area of 75 km². Wikipedia

Au peninsula.label: Au peninsula
Au peninsula.description: The Au peninsula is located in the Swiss Lake Zürich at the municipality Au between Wädenswil and Horgen in the Canton of Zurich. Wikipedia

Banda Islands.label: Banda Islands
Banda Islands.description: The Banda Islands are a volcanic group of ten small volcanic islands in the Banda Sea, about 140 km south of Seram Island and about 2,000 km east of Java, and are part of the Indonesian province of Maluku. Wikipedia

Bering Island.label: Bering Island
Bering Island.description: Bering Island is located off the Kamchatka Peninsula in the Bering Sea. Wikipedia

Berlengas.label: Berlengas
Berlengas.description: The Berlengas archipelago is a group of small islands 10 to 15 kilometers off the Portuguese coast, west of the town of Peniche in Oeste region. These islands were traditionally known to British mariners as "the Burlings". Wikipedia

Blake Island.label: Blake Island
Blake Island.description: Blake Island is an island in Kitsap County in Washington state in the United States. It lies in the middle of Puget Sound, north of Vashon Island, south of Bainbridge Island and east of Manchester. Wikipedia

Brač.label: Brač
Brač.description: Brač is an island in the Adriatic Sea within Croatia, with an area of 396 square kilometres, making it the largest island in Dalmatia, and the third largest in the Adriatic. Wikipedia

Bremen Island.label: Bremen Island
Bremen Island.description:
Bremen Island is a 1 km² or 100 ha uninhabited island, part of the Melchior Islands in the Southern Ocean along the west coast of the Antarctic Peninsula.
A 1 km long channel separates Omega Island and Bremen Island. Wikipedia

Byam Martin Island.label: Byam Martin Island
Byam Martin Island.description: Byam Martin Island is one of the Canadian arctic islands located on the northern side of the Viscount Melville Sound in the territory of Nunavut. Wikipedia

Camano Island.label: Camano Island
Camano Island.description: Camano Island is a large island in the Possession Sound portion of Puget Sound, located in Island County, Washington, between Whidbey Island and the mainland. The body of water separating Whidbey Island and Camano Island is called Saratoga Passage. Wikipedia

Chirinkotan.label: Chirinkotan
Chirinkotan.description: Chirinkotan is an uninhabited volcanic island located in the centre of the Kuril Islands chain in the Sea of Okhotsk in the northwest Pacific Ocean. Its name is derived from the Ainu language for "mudslide". Wikipedia

Coats Island.label: Coats Island
Coats Island.description: Coats Island lies at the northern end of Hudson Bay in the Kivalliq Region of Nunavut. At 5,498 km² in size, it is the 107th largest island in the world, and Canada's 24th largest island. Wikipedia

Corvo Island.label: Corvo Island
Corvo Island.description: Corvo Island, literally the Island of the Crow, is the smallest and the northernmost island of the Azores archipelago and the northernmost in Macaronesia, with a population of approximately 468 inhabitants ... Wikipedia

Düne.label: Dune
Düne.description: In physical geography, a dune is a hill of sand built by either wind or water flow. Dunes occur in different forms and sizes, formed by interaction with the flow of air or water. Wikipedia

Cosmoledo.label: Cosmoledo
Cosmoledo.description:
Cosmoledo is an atoll of the Aldabra Group and belongs to the Outer Islands of the Seychelles.
The atoll is 14.5 km long east-west, and 11.5 km north-south. The total land area is about 5.2 km², while the lagoon measures 145 km² in area. Wikipedia

D'Urville Island, New Zealand.label: D'Urville Island, New Zealand
D'Urville Island, New Zealand.description: D'Urville Island is an island in the Marlborough Sounds along the northern coast of the South Island of New Zealand. It was named after the French explorer Jules Dumont d'Urville. Wikipedia

Dugi otok.label: Dugi otok
Dugi otok.description: Dugi Otok is the seventh largest island in the Adriatic Sea, part of Croatia. It is located off the Dalmatian coast, west of Zadar. It is the largest and easternmost of the Zadarian Islands, and derives its name from its distinctive shape. Wikipedia

East Burra.label: East Burra
East Burra.description:
East Burra is one of the Scalloway Islands, a subgroup of the Shetland Islands in Scotland. It is connected by a bridge to West Burra.
With an area of 515 hectares it is the twelfth largest of the Shetland Islands. Wikipedia

Eglinton Island.label: Eglinton Island
Eglinton Island.description: Eglinton Island an uninhabited island of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago in the Northwest Territories, Canada. Eglinton is one of the Queen Elizabeth Islands. Wikipedia

Eilean Donan.label: Eilean Donan
Eilean Donan.description: Eilean Donan is a small tidal island where three lochs meet, Loch Duich, Loch Long and Loch Alsh, in the western Highlands of Scotland; since the castle's restoration in the early 20th Century, a footbridge has connected the island to the mainland. Wikipedia

Fair Isle.label: Fair Isle
Fair Isle.description: Fair Isle is an island in northern Scotland, lying around halfway between mainland Shetland and the Orkney islands. It is famous for its bird observatory and a traditional style of knitting. Wikipedia

Fasta Åland.label: Fasta Åland
Fasta Åland.description: Fasta Åland is the largest and most populous island of Åland, an autonomous province of Finland. The provincial capital Mariehamn is located on the island. With the area of 685 km² it is the 3rd largest island in Finland. Wikipedia

Fogo, Cape Verde.label: Fogo
Fogo, Cape Verde.description: Fogo is the most prominent island of the Sotavento group of Cape Verde it rises to nearly 3,000 m above sea level at its summit, Pico do Fogo. Wikipedia

Fora Islet.label: Fora Islet
Fora Islet.description: Fora Islet, in Portuguese Ilhéu de Fora, is an uninhabited Portuguese island in the Atlantic Ocean, forming part of the Savage Islands, a dependant archipelago of the autonomous region of Madeira. Wikipedia

Fraser Island.label: Fraser Island
Fraser Island.description: Fraser Island is a heritage-listed island located along the southern coast of Queensland, Australia, approximately 200 kilometres north of Brisbane. It is a locality within the Fraser Coast Region. Wikipedia

Geography of the Isle of Man.label: Geography of the Isle of Man
Geography of the Isle of Man.description: The Isle of Man is an island in the Irish Sea, between Great Britain and Ireland in Western Europe, with a population of over 75,000. It is a British Crown dependency. It has a small islet, the Calf of Man, to its south. Wikipedia

Giannutri.label: Giannutri
Giannutri.description: Giannutri is a small island in the Mediterranean Sea off the coast of Tuscany, Italy. It is the most southerly island of the Tuscan Archipelago and was known as Dianium by Romans and Artemisia, Αρτεμησία by Greeks. Wikipedia

Hashima Island.label: Hashima Island
Hashima Island.description: Hashima Island, commonly called Gunkanjima, is one among 505 uninhabited islands in Nagasaki Prefecture about 15 kilometers from Nagasaki itself. Wikipedia

Ilheu Bom Bom.label: Ilheu Bom Bom
Ilheu Bom Bom.description: Ilhéu Bom Bom, also written as Ilhéu Bombom, is an island in the Gulf of Guinea. The islet is located north of the coast of the island of Príncipe, one of the main islands of São Tomé and Príncipe. Wikipedia

Jeju Province.label: Jeju Province
Jeju Province.description: Jeju Province is one of the nine provinces of South Korea. The province is situated on and coterminous with the nation's largest island of Jeju, formerly transliterated as Cheju, Cheju Do, etc., or known as Quelpart to Europeans. Wikipedia

Kharimkotan.label: Kharimkotan
Kharimkotan.description: Kharimkotan; Japanese 春牟古丹島; Harimukotan-tō, alternatively Harumukotan-tō or 加林古丹島; Karinkotan-tō is an uninhabited volcanic island located 13 kilometres km from Onekotan near the northern end of the Kuril Islands chain in the Sea of Okhotsk in the ... Wikipedia

Khortytsia.label: Khortytsia
Khortytsia.description:
Khortytsia is a national cultural reserve located on one of the largest islands of the Dnieper river, in Ukraine.
The island has played an important role in the history of Ukraine, specially in the history of the Zaporozhian Cossacks. Wikipedia

King Christian Island.label: King Christian Island
King Christian Island.description: King Christian Island is an uninhabited member of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago in the Sverdrup Islands, a part of the Queen Elizabeth Islands archipelago, in the Qikiqtaaluk Region of Nunavut, Canada. Wikipedia

Kuhn Island.label: Kuhn Island
Kuhn Island.description: Kuhn Island is an island in eastern Greenland. There are coal deposits on the island. Wikipedia

La Tortuga Island.label: La Tortuga Island
La Tortuga Island.description: La Tortuga Island is an uninhabited island dependent on the government of Venezuela. It is part of a chain of islands that include the Tortuguillas, the Palaquines, and others. Has an area of 156 km² Wikipedia

List of islands of Michigan.label: Lake Michigan
List of islands of Michigan.description: Lake Michigan is one of the five Great Lakes of North America and the only one located entirely within the United States. The other four Great Lakes are shared by the U.S. and Canada. Wikipedia

Los Roques archipelago.label: Los Roques archipelago
Los Roques archipelago.description: Los Roques archipelago is a federal dependency of Venezuela consisting of approximately 350 islands, cays, and islets in a total area of 40.61 square kilometers. The archipelago is located 128 kilometers directly north of the port of La Guaira. Wikipedia

Lougheed Island.label: Lougheed Island
Lougheed Island.description: Lougheed Island is one of the uninhabited islands of the Canadian Arctic Archipelago in the Qikiqtaaluk Region, Nunavut. It measures 1,312 km² in size. Wikipedia

Macauley Island.label: Macauley Island
Macauley Island.description: Macauley Island is a volcanic island in New Zealand's Kermadec Islands, approximately halfway between New Zealand's North Island and Tonga in the southwest Pacific Ocean. Wikipedia

Mackenzie King Island.label: Mackenzie King Island
Mackenzie King Island.description: Mackenzie King Island is one of the Queen Elizabeth Islands in northern Canada. It lies north of Melville Island and south of Borden Island, and like them is divided. Wikipedia

Mainland, Orkney.label: Mainland, Orkney
Mainland, Orkney.description: The Mainland is the main island of Orkney. Both of Orkney's burghs, Kirkwall and Stromness, lie on the island, which is also the heart of Orkney's ferry and air connections. Wikipedia

Mainland, Shetland.label: Shetland Mainland
Mainland, Shetland.description: The Mainland is the main island of Shetland, Scotland. The island contains Shetland's only burgh, Lerwick, and is the centre of Shetland's ferry and air connections. Wikipedia

Makanrushi.label: Makanrushi
Makanrushi.description: Makanrushi is an uninhabited volcanic island located near the northern end of the Kuril Islands chain in the Sea of Okhotsk in the northwest Pacific Ocean. Its name is derived from the Ainu language. Wikipedia

Manitoulin Island.label: Manitoulin Island
Manitoulin Island.description: Manitoulin Island is a Canadian lake island in Lake Huron, in the province of Ontario. It is the largest fresh water lake island in the world. Wikipedia

Massey Island.label: Massey Island
Massey Island.description: Massey Island is an uninhabited island in the Bathurst Island group, Qikiqtaaluk Region, Nunavut, Canada. It is located in the Arctic Ocean, south of Île Vanier and north of Alexander Island and Île Marc. Wikipedia

Melville Island (Australia).label: Melville Island
Melville Island (Australia).description: Melville Island known in the Tiwi language as Yermalner lies in the eastern Timor Sea, off the coast of the Northern Territory, Australia. It is west of the Cobourg Peninsula in Arnhem Land and north of Darwin. Wikipedia

Minsener Oog.label: Minsener Oog
Minsener Oog.description: Minsener Oog, also Minser Oog or Minsener Oldeoog, is an uninhabited East Frisian island, that belongs to the parish of Wangerooge in the north German district of Friesland in the state of Lower Saxony. Wikipedia

Muck, Scotland.label: Muck, Scotland
Muck, Scotland.description: Muck is the smallest of four main islands in the Small Isles, part of the Inner Hebrides of Scotland. It measures roughly 2.5 miles east to west and has a population of around 30, mostly living near the harbour at Port Mòr. Wikipedia

Muckle Roe.label: Muckle Roe
Muckle Roe.description: Muckle Roe is an island in Shetland, Scotland, in St. Magnus Bay, to the west of Mainland, Shetland. It has a population of around 130 people, who mainly croft and live in the south east of the island. Wikipedia

Nansen Island.label: Nansen Island
Nansen Island.description: Nansen Island or Isla Nansen Sur is the largest of the islands lying in Wilhelmina Bay off the west coast of Graham Land, lying 4 miles east of Emma Island. Wikipedia

Munkholmen.label: Munkholmen
Munkholmen.description: Munkholmen is an islet north of Trondheim, Norway. It sits in the Trondheimsfjord about 1.3 kilometres northwest of the island of Brattøra and the mouth of the river Nidelva. Wikipedia

Oak Island.label: Oak Island
Oak Island.description: Oak Island is a 57-hectare island in Lunenburg County on the south shore of Nova Scotia, Canada. The tree-covered island is one of about 360 small islands in Mahone Bay and rises to a maximum of 11 meters above sea level. Wikipedia

Papa Stour.label: Papa Stour
Papa Stour.description: Papa Stour is one of the Shetland Islands in Scotland, with a population of under twenty people, some of whom immigrated after an appeal for residents in the 1970s. Wikipedia

Osmussaar.label: Osmussaar
Osmussaar.description: Osmussaar is an Estonian island situated in the mouth of the Gulf of Finland in the Baltic Sea, 7.5 km off the Estonian mainland. Administratively the island is part of Noarootsi Parish in Lääne County. Its area is 4.8 km². Wikipedia

Papa Stronsay.label: Papa Stronsay
Papa Stronsay.description:
Papa Stronsay is a small island in Orkney, Scotland, lying north east of Stronsay. It is 74 hectares in size, and 13 metres at its highest point.
According to folklore, some of the natives were descended from a female selkie. Wikipedia

Paramushir.label: Paramushir
Paramushir.description: Paramushir, is a volcanic island in the northern portion of Kuril Islands chain in the Sea of Okhotsk in the northwest Pacific Ocean. Wikipedia

Rügen.label: Rügen
Rügen.description: Rügen is Germany's largest island by area. It is located off the Pomeranian coast in the Baltic Sea and belongs to the state of Mecklenburg-Western Pomerania. Wikipedia

Riether Werder.label: Riether Werder
Riether Werder.description: The Riether Werder, also Riethscher Werder, is an island in the Neuwarper See, a bay in the Stettin Lagoon. It is the only island in the lagoon on German territory. Wikipedia

Ringgold Isles.label: Ringgold Isles
Ringgold Isles.description: The Ringgold Isles are an archipelago in Fiji, forming an outlier group to Vanua Levu. The Budd, Nukusemanu, and Heemskercq Reefs form part of the group. The group is mostly uninhabited, but Qelelevu has a small village. Wikipedia

Rota (island).label: Rota
Rota (island).description: Rota also known as the “Peaceful Island”, is the southernmost island of the United States Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands and the second southernmost of the Marianas Archipelago. Wikipedia

Sal, Cape Verde.label: Sal
Sal, Cape Verde.description: Sal is an island in Cape Verde. It belongs to the northern group of islands, called Barlavento, and comprises a single administrative division, the Sal municipality. Wikipedia

São Vicente, Cape Verde.label: São Vicente
São Vicente, Cape Verde.description: São Vicente, also Son Visent or Son Sent in Cape Verdean Creole, is one of the Barlavento islands of Cape Verde. It is located between the islands of Santo Antão and Santa Luzia, with the Canal de São Vicente separating it from Santo Antão. Wikipedia

Samsø.label: Samsø
Samsø.description: Samsø is a Danish island in the Kattegat 15 kilometers off the Jutland Peninsula. Samsø is located in Samsø municipality. The community has 3,806 inhabitants called Samsings and is 114 km² in area. Wikipedia

Scott Island.label: Scott Island
Scott Island.description: Scott Island is a small uninhabited island of volcanic origin in the Ross Sea, Southern Ocean, 505 kilometres northeast of Cape Adare, the northeastern extremity of Victoria Land, Antarctica. Wikipedia

San Juan Island.label: San Juan Island
San Juan Island.description: San Juan Island is the second-largest and most populous of the San Juan Islands in northwestern Washington, United States. It has a land area of 142.59 km² and a population of 6,822 as of the 2000 census. Wikipedia

Shiashkotan.label: Shiashkotan
Shiashkotan.description: Shiashkotan; is an uninhabited volcanic island near the center of the Kuril Islands chain in the Sea of Okhotsk in the northwest Pacific Ocean, separated from Ekarma by the Ekarma Strait. Wikipedia

North Sentinel Island.label: North Sentinel Island
North Sentinel Island.description: North Sentinel Island is one of the Andaman Islands in the Bay of Bengal. It lies to the west of the southern part of South Andaman Island. Most of the island is forested. Wikipedia

Shapinsay.label: Shapinsay
Shapinsay.description: Shapinsay is one of the Orkney Islands off the north coast of mainland Scotland. There is one village on the island, Balfour, from which roll-on/roll-off car ferries sail to Kirkwall on the Orkney Mainland. Wikipedia

Sveti Grgur.label: Sveti Grgur
Sveti Grgur.description: Sveti Grgur is an uninhabited island in Croatia, on the Adriatic Sea between Rab and Krk. The island was the site of a women's prison in communist Yugoslavia from 1948 to 1988. Wikipedia

Svenskøya.label: Svenskøya
Svenskøya.description:
Svenskøya is an island in Svalbard. It is the second largest island of King Charles Land with an area of 137 km².
Svenskøya is separated from Kongsøya by the strait Rivalensundet. Wikipedia

Umm an Nasan.label: Umm an Nasan
Umm an Nasan.description: Umm an Nasan island is the fourth largest island in Bahrain, after Bahrain Island, Hawar Island and Muharraq Island. It is privately owned by King Hamad bin Isa Al Khalifa, and is off limits to ordinary citizens. Wikipedia

Utøya.label: Utøya
Utøya.description: Utøya is an island in the Tyrifjorden lake in Hole municipality, in the county of Buskerud, Norway. Wikipedia

Vanua Lava.label: Vanua Lava
Vanua Lava.description:
Vanua Lava is the second largest of the Banks Islands in Torba Province, Vanuatu, after slightly larger Gaua.
It is located about 120 km north-northeast of Espiritu Santo and north of Gaua. Wikipedia

Werd (Lake Constance).label: Werd
Werd (Lake Constance).description: Werd Island is the main island of the small island group Werd Islands in the westernmost part of the Lower Lake of Lake Constance just before the High Rhine leaves the part of the lake known as Rheinsee. Wikipedia

West Burra.label: West Burra
West Burra.description: West Burra is one of the Scalloway Islands, a subgroup of the Shetland Islands in Scotland. It is connected by bridge to East Burra. With an area of 743 hectares, it is the eleventh largest of the Shetland Islands. Wikipedia

Whidbey Island.label: Whidbey Island
Whidbey Island.description: Whidbey Island is the largest of the two islands located in Island County, Washington, in the United States. Whidbey is about 30 miles north of Seattle, and lies between the Olympic Peninsula and the I-5 corridor of western Washington. Wikipedia

Öland.label: Öland
Öland.description: Öland is the second largest Swedish island and the smallest of the traditional provinces of Sweden. Öland has an area of 1,342 km² and is located in the Baltic Sea just off the coast of Småland. Wikipedia

ʻEua.label: ʻEua
ʻEua.description: ʻEua is a smaller but still major island in the kingdom of Tonga. It is close to Tongatapu, but forms a separate administrative division. It has an area of 87.44 km², and a population in 2011 of 5,016 people. Wikipedia

Adelaide Island.label: Adelaide Island
Adelaide Island.description: Adelaide Island or Isla Adelaida or Isla Belgrano is a large, mainly ice-covered island, 120 kilometres long and 32 kilometres wide, lying at the north side of Marguerite Bay off the west coast of the Antarctic Peninsula. Wikipedia

Austral Islands.label: Austral Islands
Austral Islands.description: The Tuha'a Pae or Austral Islands are the southernmost group of islands in French Polynesia, an overseas collectivity of France in the South Pacific. Wikipedia

Baffin Island.label: Baffin Island
Baffin Island.description: Baffin Island, in the Canadian territory of Nunavut, is the largest island in Canada and the fifth largest island in the world. Its area is 507,451 km² and its population is about 11,000. Wikipedia

Banaba Island.label: Banaba Island
Banaba Island.description: Banaba Island, an island in the Pacific Ocean, is a solitary raised coral island west of the Gilbert Island chain and 185 miles east of Nauru. It is part of the Republic of Kiribati. Wikipedia

Bass Rock.label: Bass Rock
Bass Rock.description: The Bass Rock, or simply the Bass, is an island in the outer part of the Firth of Forth in the east of Scotland. It is approximately 2 kilometres offshore, and 5 kilometres north-east of North Berwick. Wikipedia

St. Lawrence Island.label: St. Lawrence Island
St. Lawrence Island.description: St. Lawrence Island is located west of mainland Alaska in the Bering Sea, just south of the Bering Strait, at about 63°30' North 173°20' West. Wikipedia

South Ronaldsay.label: South Ronaldsay
South Ronaldsay.description: South Ronaldsay is one of the Orkney Islands off the north coast of Scotland. It is linked to the Orkney Mainland by the Churchill Barriers, running via Burray, Glimps Holm and Lamb Holm. Wikipedia

Soay, St Kilda.label: Soay, St Kilda
Soay, St Kilda.description: Soay is an uninhabited islet in the St Kilda archipelago, Scotland. Soay is Old Norse, meaning "Island of Sheep". The island is part of the St Kilda World Heritage Site and home to a primitive breed of sheep. Wikipedia

North Ronaldsay.label: North Ronaldsay
North Ronaldsay.description: North Ronaldsay is the northernmost of the Orkney Islands and, with an area of 2.7 square kilometres, is the fourteenth largest. Wikipedia

Nordenskiöld Archipelago.label: Nordenskiöld Archipelago
Nordenskiöld Archipelago.description: The Nordenskiöld Archipelago or Nordenskjold Archipelago is a very large and complex cluster of islands in the eastern region of the Kara Sea. Its eastern limit lies 120 km west of the Taymyr Peninsula. Wikipedia
